#: ../../../style-guide.rst:5
msgid "Style Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:9
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:11
msgid ""
"This guide is intended to provide coding conventions for writing Solidity "
"code. This guide should be thought of as an evolving document that will "
"change over time as useful conventions are found and old conventions are "
"rendered obsolete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:15
msgid ""
"Many projects will implement their own style guides.  In the event of "
"conflicts, project specific style guides take precedence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:18
msgid ""
"The structure and many of the recommendations within this style guide were "
"taken from Python's `pep8 style guide <https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:22
msgid ""
"The goal of this guide is *not* to be the right way or the best way to write "
"Solidity code.  The goal of this guide is *consistency*.  A quote from "
"Python's `pep8 <https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#a-foolish-consistency-is-"
"the-hobgoblin-of-little-minds>`_ captures this concept well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:29
msgid ""
"A style guide is about consistency. Consistency with this style guide is "
"important. Consistency within a project is more important. Consistency "
"within one module or function is most important."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:31
msgid ""
"But most importantly: **know when to be inconsistent** -- sometimes the "
"style guide just doesn't apply. When in doubt, use your best judgment. Look "
"at other examples and decide what looks best. And do not hesitate to ask!"
msgstr ""

