#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1100
msgid "Naming Conventions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1102
msgid ""
"Naming conventions are powerful when adopted and used broadly.  The use of "
"different conventions can convey significant *meta* information that would "
"otherwise not be immediately available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1106
msgid ""
"The naming recommendations given here are intended to improve the "
"readability, and thus they are not rules, but rather guidelines to try and "
"help convey the most information through the names of things."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1110
msgid ""
"Lastly, consistency within a codebase should always supersede any "
"conventions outlined in this document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1115
msgid "Naming Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1117
msgid ""
"To avoid confusion, the following names will be used to refer to different "
"naming styles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1120
msgid "``b`` (single lowercase letter)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1121
msgid "``B`` (single uppercase letter)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1122
msgid "``lowercase``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1123
msgid "``UPPERCASE``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1124
msgid "``UPPER_CASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1125
msgid "``CapitalizedWords`` (or CapWords)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1126
msgid ""
"``mixedCase`` (differs from CapitalizedWords by initial lowercase character!)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1128
msgid ""
"When using initialisms in CapWords, capitalize all the letters of the "
"initialisms. Thus HTTPServerError is better than HttpServerError. When using "
"initialisms in mixedCase, capitalize all the letters of the initialisms, "
"except keep the first one lower case if it is the beginning of the name. "
"Thus xmlHTTPRequest is better than XMLHTTPRequest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1132
msgid "Names to Avoid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1134
msgid "``l`` - Lowercase letter el"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1135
msgid "``O`` - Uppercase letter oh"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1136
msgid "``I`` - Uppercase letter eye"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1138
msgid ""
"Never use any of these for single letter variable names.  They are often "
"indistinguishable from the numerals one and zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1143
msgid "Contract and Library Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1145
msgid ""
"Contracts and libraries should be named using the CapWords style. Examples: "
"``SimpleToken``, ``SmartBank``, ``CertificateHashRepository``, ``Player``, "
"``Congress``, ``Owned``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1146
msgid "Contract and library names should also match their filenames."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1147
msgid ""
"If a contract file includes multiple contracts and/or libraries, then the "
"filename should match the *core contract*. This is not recommended however "
"if it can be avoided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1149
msgid ""
"As shown in the example below, if the contract name is ``Congress`` and the "
"library name is ``Owned``, then their associated filenames should be "
"``Congress.sol`` and ``Owned.sol``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1153
msgid ""
"// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\n"
"pragma solidity >=0.7.0 <0.9.0;\n"
"\n"
"// Owned.sol\n"
"contract Owned {\n"
"    address public owner;\n"
"\n"
"    modifier onlyOwner {\n"
"        require(msg.sender == owner);\n"
"        _;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    constructor() {\n"
"        owner = msg.sender;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    function transferOwnership(address newOwner) public onlyOwner {\n"
"        owner = newOwner;\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1176 ../../../style-guide.rst:1215
msgid "and in ``Congress.sol``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1178
msgid ""
"// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\n"
"pragma solidity >=0.4.0 <0.9.0;\n"
"\n"
"import \"./Owned.sol\";\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"contract Congress is Owned, TokenRecipient {\n"
"    //...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1192
msgid ""
"// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\n"
"pragma solidity >=0.7.0 <0.9.0;\n"
"\n"
"// owned.sol\n"
"contract owned {\n"
"    address public owner;\n"
"\n"
"    modifier onlyOwner {\n"
"        require(msg.sender == owner);\n"
"        _;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    constructor() {\n"
"        owner = msg.sender;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    function transferOwnership(address newOwner) public onlyOwner {\n"
"        owner = newOwner;\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1217
msgid ""
"// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\n"
"pragma solidity ^0.7.0;\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"import \"./owned.sol\";\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"contract Congress is owned, tokenRecipient {\n"
"    //...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1231
msgid "Struct Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1233
msgid ""
"Structs should be named using the CapWords style. Examples: ``MyCoin``, "
"``Position``, ``PositionXY``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1237
msgid "Event Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1239
msgid ""
"Events should be named using the CapWords style. Examples: ``Deposit``, "
"``Transfer``, ``Approval``, ``BeforeTransfer``, ``AfterTransfer``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1243
msgid "Function Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1245
msgid ""
"Functions should use mixedCase. Examples: ``getBalance``, ``transfer``, "
"``verifyOwner``, ``addMember``, ``changeOwner``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1249
msgid "Function Argument Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1251
msgid ""
"Function arguments should use mixedCase. Examples: ``initialSupply``, "
"``account``, ``recipientAddress``, ``senderAddress``, ``newOwner``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1253
msgid ""
"When writing library functions that operate on a custom struct, the struct "
"should be the first argument and should always be named ``self``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1258
msgid "Local and State Variable Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1260
msgid ""
"Use mixedCase. Examples: ``totalSupply``, ``remainingSupply``, "
"``balancesOf``, ``creatorAddress``, ``isPreSale``, ``tokenExchangeRate``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1264
msgid "Constants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1266
msgid ""
"Constants should be named with all capital letters with underscores "
"separating words. Examples: ``MAX_BLOCKS``, ``TOKEN_NAME``, "
"``TOKEN_TICKER``, ``CONTRACT_VERSION``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1271
msgid "Modifier Names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1273
msgid ""
"Use mixedCase. Examples: ``onlyBy``, ``onlyAfter``, ``onlyDuringThePreSale``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1277
msgid "Enums"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1279
msgid ""
"Enums, in the style of simple type declarations, should be named using the "
"CapWords style. Examples: ``TokenGroup``, ``Frame``, ``HashStyle``, "
"``CharacterLocation``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1283
msgid "Avoiding Naming Collisions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1285
msgid "``singleTrailingUnderscore_``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1287
msgid ""
"This convention is suggested when the desired name collides with that of an "
"existing state variable, function, built-in or otherwise reserved name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1291
msgid "Underscore Prefix for Non-external Functions and Variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1293
msgid "``_singleLeadingUnderscore``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1295
msgid ""
"This convention is suggested for non-external functions and state variables "
"(``private`` or ``internal``). State variables without a specified "
"visibility are ``internal`` by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1297
msgid ""
"When designing a smart contract, the public-facing API (functions that can "
"be called by any account) is an important consideration. Leading underscores "
"allow you to immediately recognize the intent of such functions, but more "
"importantly, if you change a function from non-external to external "
"(including ``public``) and rename it accordingly, this forces you to review "
"every call site while renaming. This can be an important manual check "
"against unintended external functions and a common source of security "
"vulnerabilities (avoid find-replace-all tooling for this change)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1309
msgid "NatSpec"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1311
msgid ""
"Solidity contracts can also contain NatSpec comments. They are written with "
"a triple slash (``///``) or a double asterisk block (``/** ... */``) and "
"they should be used directly above function declarations or statements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1315
msgid ""
"For example, the contract from :ref:`a simple smart contract <simple-smart-"
"contract>` with the comments added looks like the one below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1318
msgid ""
"// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\n"
"pragma solidity >=0.4.16 <0.9.0;\n"
"\n"
"/// @author The Solidity Team\n"
"/// @title A simple storage example\n"
"contract SimpleStorage {\n"
"    uint storedData;\n"
"\n"
"    /// Store `x`.\n"
"    /// @param x the new value to store\n"
"    /// @dev stores the number in the state variable `storedData`\n"
"    function set(uint x) public {\n"
"        storedData = x;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    /// Return the stored value.\n"
"    /// @dev retrieves the value of the state variable `storedData`\n"
"    /// @return the stored value\n"
"    function get() public view returns (uint) {\n"
"        return storedData;\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1343
msgid ""
"It is recommended that Solidity contracts are fully annotated using :ref:"
"`NatSpec <natspec>` for all public interfaces (everything in the ABI)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:1345
msgid ""
"Please see the section about :ref:`NatSpec <natspec>` for a detailed "
"explanation."
msgstr ""

